# content-copy.mdc
## Content & Copy Standards

### REQUIRED
- No hyphens in any copy (rewrite to avoid them entirely)
- Active voice preferred over passive
- Sentence case for headings (not Title Case)
- Oxford comma always
- Direct, no nonsense tone

### BIOTECH/HEALTHCARE CONTENT
- Technical accuracy over marketing language
- Cite sources for scientific claims
- Use researcher friendly terminology
- Avoid overpromising outcomes
- Lead with the problem, then the solution

### SEO CONTENT
- Primary keyword in H1
- Secondary keywords distributed naturally in H2s
- Meta descriptions under 160 characters
- Alt text describes image function, not just appearance
- Internal linking to related service pages

### TONE BY CONTEXT
- Lab Signals: Authoritative but accessible, researcher peer voice
- ITL service pages: Professional, technical, solution oriented
- Client facing (UXUI Design Corp): Confident, results focused
- Venue/wedding: Warm, aspirational, detail oriented

### FORBIDDEN
- Hyphens (always find alternative phrasing)
- Passive voice when active voice works
- Marketing superlatives without substantiation
- Jargon without explanation for general audiences
- Filler phrases ("in order to", "due to the fact that")
- Weak hedging language ("maybe", "perhaps", "might")
